<header class="border-b hairline bg-[var(--color-page-dark)]">
  <div class="container-wide pt-14 pb-12 md:pt-20 md:pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">A companion site to a reimplementation of IncPy</p>
    <h1 class="h-display max-w-[26ch]">
      A cache for the slow functions in your Python scripts.
    </h1>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      You point <code>rote</code> at any Python script. As the script runs, it watches each
      function call. If the call took meaningful time and the function looks safe to cache,
      the return value gets written to disk. The next run reuses those stored values for any
      function whose source code and inputs haven't changed; everything else runs as usual.
      The design is from a 2011 paper by Philip Guo and David Engler called
      <em>IncPy</em>. This page is the comparison.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>
